cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Multi-parameter Mach-Zehnder estimation: numerical exploration"
message: >-
  If you use this code in research, please cite both this repository and
  the associated 2020 M.Sc. thesis.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Qureshi
    given-names: Hamza
    email: thehamzaq@gmail.com
  - name: "Anthropic Claude (AI assistant)"
    affiliation: "AI assistant; co-author per ICMJE guidance is not appropriate"
license: GPL-3.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/thehamzaq/mz-multiparameter"
references:
  - type: thesis
    title: "Variable Beam-Splitter Reflectivity Estimation for Interferometry"
    authors:
      - family-names: Qureshi
        given-names: Hamza
        email: thehamzaq@gmail.com
    year: 2020
    institution:
      name: "University of Calgary, Department of Physics and Astronomy"
    url: "https://ucalgary.scholaris.ca/items/f65d88e6-50cb-4ef9-8ece-a6de6895717d"
abstract: >-
  Python toolkit and reproducible experiments for two-parameter (beam-splitter
  reflectivity, phase) Mach-Zehnder quantum metrology with twin-Fock probes,
  including symmetric and asymmetric photon loss and Jz-dephasing. Numerical
  observations include: minimal 2-observable method-of-moments readout
  saturating the joint Cramér-Rao bound; Holevo bound coincides with SLD bound
  numerically under photon loss; exact invariance of the reflectivity quantum
  Fisher information under one-arm photon loss and arbitrary Jz-dephasing.
  Largely AI-generated; not yet peer-reviewed.
